            <h1 class="webcast-title">ISSA International Series: Trials &amp; Tribulations of Social Engineering</h1>
                        <div ng-cloak class="webcast-description-wrapper" ng-class="{'webcast-description-collapsed': !webcast.description.expanded && '1'}">
                <div>
                    <span class="webcast-description">We all know about social engineering and phishing; but âIs it as simple as sending an email or asking for a click?â probably not.  As hackers and attacks evolve, they will go from simple tricks to very sophisticated attacks.  So how do we know what these attacks will be?  Simply, we canât.  So how can we detect the new attacks?  This session will cover the state of the attacks and the directions they are taking.  Ultimately, we will discuss strategies and how we can define the science that will evolve to thwart the evolving various attacks<br />
<br />
Moderated by: Pete Lindstrom, IDC<br />
<br />
Presenters: <br />
<br />
Roger Grimes, Data-Driven Defense Evangelist, KnowBe4<br />
Andrew Lewman, Laxdaela Technology<br />
Ben Rothke, Senior Security Consultant, Nettitude<br />
Paul Williams, CEO, Clarity Consulting Corporation</span>
                </div>
            </div>

